item.title: Community library master branch
item.dc:creator: @thetechnobear Mark Harris
item.description:
@thetechnobear wrote:

1.0.9 - and no-one should be using it anymore , since they should have upgraded to 1.0.10 by now.

we clearly stated, all test releases should be upgrade to 1.0.10,
see http://community.axoloti.com/t/axoloti-test-release-1-0-10/
from 1.0.10 onwards the master branch will not be used by the community library.
(its possible we may use it for development , but thats not definite yet)

test releases are always expected to be upgrade in a short while after a new test release is released,
since its not 'viable' to support multiple test releases, they are 'merely' for testing. we have made this clear for each test release.

(yeah, i know this 'test phase' has gone on longer than we would like too)

of course, 1.06 can also be used (but does not feature the library) as this is the latest stable release.
